  "issue_number": 118,
  "issue_title": "feature: add next-step context and clarification path",
  "issue_body": "## Problem\n\nA multi-step local agent must use what happened in the previous step. It also needs a safe path when the next action is uncertain or multiple targets match. Without that, the loop will either guess or stop with vague errors.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nAdd a next-step context object that carries recent screen summary, selected tool result, verification result, failure reason, and candidate targets into the next local decision. Add a clarification decision path when the local router cannot safely choose one action.\n\nClarification cases should include:\n\n- multiple matching targets\n- missing required target\n- ambiguous user request\n- low confidence local decision\n- action would require user choice before continuing\n\n## User workflow\n\nWhen TouchPilot is unsure, it asks a direct question such as \u201cWhich Settings item should I open?\u201d instead of executing a risky or random action.\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nThis improves small local model reliability by giving it structured context and a non-execution fallback.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\nClarification must not expose raw sensitive screen text. If policy blocks the action, the loop should stop or ask for approval only through the existing approval path, not through generic clarification.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Adds a reusable next-step context structure.\n- Carries tool result and verification result into the next decision.\n- Adds clarification decision type and stop/continue behavior.\n- Includes tests for ambiguous target and no-valid-action cases.\n- Keeps blocked-policy behavior distinct from clarification behavior.",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-27T20:43:28.000Z",
